ads/2020/01/1-Why-Wont-My-Garage-Door-Go-Up-1.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT806w4JgH1n0tCw7IO5QzHa-sE1jUNdRinmQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:442;s:6:"height";i:1133;s:6:"source";s:60:"https://www.doorpros.com/blog/why-wont-my-garage-door-go-up/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"www.doorpros.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:61:{i:0;s:123:"The most common reason why the garage door opens a few inches and then stops is most likely because of the spring assembly.";i:1;s:137:"If garage door springs are not adjusted correctly the doors arent able to open because there is too much weight for the opener to handle.";i:2;s:102:"My garage door only opens a couple of inches and stops Posted by Ali Tyler on Wed Oct 01 2014 0107 PM.";i:3;s:67:"This is another very common problem we hear described by customers.";i:4;s:114:"Unfortunately this problem is not usually a do-it yourself fix like the safety photo sensors we talked about in a.";i:5;s:118:"Sometimes homeowners accidentally bump them with garbage cans rakes shovels or other objects and dont even realize it.";i:6;s:127:"Shortly after when the homeowner goes to close the Garage Door it will only close about 4-6 inches and goes right back to open.";i:7;s:66:"Simply turning them towards each other can realign the photo eyes.";i:8;s:85:"Garage Door sometimes opens a few inches and stops then closes and opens all the way.";i:9;s:96:"Can happen either from the wired connector in the garage or one of the remotes from the outside.";i:10;s:82:"Sometimes its fixed by clicking again the door closes then continues to open then.";i:11;s:44:"I have a craftsman 12 HP garage door opener.";i:12;s:123:"Recently when I tried to open the garage door with my remote the door only went up a few inches stopped and went back down.";i:13;s:88:"I tried to use the key pad and the button inside the garage and the same thing happened.";i:14;s:128:"If I have the remote in hand and push the button to open and then I help the door along by lifting up on the door it will go up.";i:15;s:80:"Liftmaster garage door only opens and shuts a few inches after gear replacement.";i:16;s:64:"I just changed out the gears with a replacement kit from Amazon.";i:17;s:57:"After I replaced the hears I hung the garage door opener.";i:18;s:113:"Now Im having and issue where the garage only opens a couple inches and then closes a couple of inches and stops.";i:19;s:27:"Garage door opener problem.";i:20;s:212:"Slipping down a few inches after opening Posted by sicboy on 51016 at 1214 pm 0 0 Our door squeaks like crazy every time it opens and closes so Sunday night I sprayed the rollers and some of the joints with WD40.";i:21;s:105:"My rolling panel garage door only opens about 6 inches and then stops - does not go back down just stops.";i:22;s:75:"I tried to spray the rollers wWD 40 and see that thats not the thing to do.";i:23;s:42:"But now Im stuck not being able to get in.";i:24;s:123:"There is nothing in the way of the sensors - although I do believe that they are primarily for safety when the door closes.";i:25;s:68:"You have an open limit and a close limit on your garage door opener.";i:26;s:74:"These limits set the distance the door will open or close before stopping.";i:27;s:199:"In the down direction if the limit is set beyond the point at which the door closes fully the door will hit the floor and act as if it is hitting something and the safety feature tells it to reverse.";i:28;s:49:"Garage door opens few inches then goes back down.";i:29;s:182:"The spring looks ok it looks like the door is out of balance on the left side I pulled the string and unhooked the garage door opener and still unable to manually lift the door open.";i:30;s:35:"It this something I can fix myself.";i:31;s:73:"The hingesrod on the top left looks to be out of place vs the other door.";i:32;s:49:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Closes Then Reopens.";i:33;s:111:"When your garage door keeps opening and closing there are typically several possibilities for this malfunction.";i:34;s:122:"If your garage door reverses when it hits the floor look into these three common causes and try troubleshooting the issue.";i:35;s:142:"Garage door will only open about 3 inches then stops This morning I opened my garage door drove out tried to close it but it refused to close.";i:36;s:135:"After a few minutes I realized one of the wires for one of the garage door eyes was covering the eye so I moved it and the door closed.";i:37;s:116:"Garage door opener craftsman model 13953930DM starts to open then stops when it gets an inch or so past the sensors.";i:38;s:59:"Sensors are glowing correctly and the door will also close.";i:39;s:56:"But the same thing happens when you go to open it again.";i:40;s:53:"Before i install new sensors am i on the right track.";i:41;s:53:"The opener mechanics seem to be functioning properly.";i:42;s:107:"As is the case with so many issues at the home theres no one reason why your garage door closes then opens.";i:43;s:70:"Heres a rundown of some of the possible reasons this can be happening.";i:44;s:46:"Your Travel Down Setting Needs to be Adjusted.";i:45;s:20:"Your garage door is.";i:46;s:51:"Have an older Touch and Go 1000 garage door opener.";i:47;s:70:"Started acting up today - will only open less than a foot then closes.";i:48;s:113:"If I catch it hit the button before it closes I can press the button again and it will go up another 6-12 inches.";i:49;s:38:"Can repeat until it is all the way up.";i:50;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:51;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:52;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:53;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:54;s:58:"At the bottom of your door theres a small infrared sensor.";i:55;s:62:"It passes a beam a few inches off the floor from side to side.";i:56;s:111:"When the door is in any position other than closed and the garage door opener is activated the door will close.";i:57;s:144:"If the garage door makes contact with an obstruction while closing the door will reverse the opener will beep and the lights will flash 5 times.";i:58;s:62:"Most garage door openers have an open and close limit control.";i:59;s:107:"They are usually on the motor housing and you access them by opening a panel or removing the housing cover.";i:60;s:140:"If the door stops short of closing lengthen the close limit by turning the control knob in the direction indicated usually counterclockwise.";}}